# Live Project Progress - Step 3 Summary

| Topic | Description | Why We Use It | Example |
|--------|-------------|---------------|----------|
| **Python** | Programming language | Write backend logic | `python app.py` |
| **Flask** | Python web framework | Build web applications | `from flask import Flask` |
| **Werkzeug** | Flask's internal WSGI library | Handles HTTP requests, responses, routing, and debugging | Installed automatically with Flask |
| **Virtual Environment (venv)** | Isolated Python environment | Avoid package conflicts and protect system Python | `python3 -m venv venv` |
| **Activate Virtual Environment** | Activates project environment | Use project-specific packages | `source venv/bin/activate` |
| **app.py** | Main Flask application | Contains routes and application logic | `app.py` |
| **Flask Application Object** | Creates the web application | Starts the Flask project | `app = Flask(__name__)` |
| **Route** | Maps URL to Python function | Defines webpages | `@app.route("/")` |
| **Home Function** | Executes when Home page is opened | Returns webpage content | `def home():` |
| **Return Statement** | Sends response to browser | Display webpage | `return "<h1>Welcome</h1>"` |
| **Debug Mode** | Development mode | Automatically reloads code after changes | `app.run(debug=True)` |
| **Flask Development Server** | Local testing server | Run application during development | `python app.py` |
| **Browser** | Client application | Sends requests and displays responses | Chrome |
| **localhost / 127.0.0.1** | Your own computer | Access local Flask application | `http://127.0.0.1:5000` |
| **Port 5000** | Default Flask port | Identifies Flask application | `127.0.0.1:5000` |
| **HTTP Request** | Browser requests webpage | Ask Flask for a page | `GET /` |
| **HTTP Response** | Flask sends webpage | Display webpage in browser | HTML Response |
| **Favicon** | Small browser tab icon | Browser automatically requests it | `favicon.ico` |
| **404 Not Found** | File not available | Indicates requested file is missing | `GET /favicon.ico 404` |

